  "bodyTextSample": "Skip to content Otty Search K Main Navigation Home Page Sidebar Navigation Getting Started Installation First Launch User Interface Window, Tab and Split Details Panel Status Bar Files and Links Drag and Drop Find Open Quickly Command Palette Outline / Jump To Workflows Recipes Session Recovery Frequent Folders Using the CLI in your Shell Data Sync SSH / Remote Development Terminal Features Cursor and Mouse Selection Scroll Input Copy and Paste Autocomplete / Inline Suggest Unicode and Text Styles Box Drawing Images Progress State Privilege and Notifications Vi Mode Hint Mode Read-only Mode Shell Integration $TERM and Identification Working with Agents Overview Setup Monitor Tasks History Composer Prompt Queue Send to Chat Fork / Branch Session Supported Agents Customization Themes Fonts and Text Rendering Keybindings Custom Commands / Layouts / Snippets Config File Advanced / All Settings Import / Export Settings Terminal API (VT) VT Overview Sequence Reference External Protocols Terminal Comparison Concepts Control ESC CSI OSC Reference CLI Reference Otty Configuration Reference Keybindings Reference Config File Format Theme Format Performance Credits About Changelog Pricing License Agreement Privacy Policy On this page Opening Find Scope Case sensitivity and regex Find in all tabs See also Find ​ In-pane search across the visible buffer and scrollback. Opening Find ​ Action Binding Open find ⌘F Next match ↩ or ⌘G Previous match ⇧↩ or ⇧⌘G Close Esc Typing into the find bar shows live results — every match is highlighted in the buffer and an inline counter shows N of M. Scope ​ Find searches the focused pane only: Terminal pane: visible viewport + full scrollback. File pane: full file. Folder pane: file names only (not contents). For searching across all tabs, see Global Search below. Case sensitivity and regex ​ The find bar has two toggles: Aa — case sensitive. .* — interpret pattern as a regular expression (Rust regex syntax). Default: case-insensitive literal. "
